# # Returns: Post object with attributes: post.id, post.title, post.content
# # Type-safe, easier to use, and less error-prone


# ============ SUMMARY ============
#
# SQLAlchemy Three-Layer Architecture:
#
# Layer 1: Engine (create_engine)
#   └─ Manages connection pooling and raw database driver
#
# Layer 2: Session Factory (sessionmaker)
#   └─ Creates Session objects for each request/conversation
#
# Layer 3: Sessions (via get_db)
#   └─ Query interface - what you use in your code
#
# Flow:
# engine ──> connection pool ──> sessionmaker ──> Session ──> Query/CRUD
#
# For FastAPI:
# Endpoint ──Depends(get_db)──> get_db() ──> Session ──> db.query(), db.add(), etc.
#
# Key Takeaway:
# SQLAlchemy lets you write Python code instead of SQL.
# It handles parameterization, type conversion, and SQL generation automatically.
